<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                                    <head>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                                    </head>
                                    <p>The funeral of King <persName>George VI</persName> was held
                                        in London on February 15. Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName> was the
                                        principal representative of President Truman. <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName>’s personal
                                        recollections of the day are to be found in <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">Acheson</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Present at the Creation</hi>, pages
                                        610–614.</p>
                                </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>